HISTORY:
******
On Nov. 20, 1990, I have released CTYHDG version 2.00 with the following
enhancements:

1. The program will now take the country description from the original
   .CTY file, rather than from the CTYHDG.PRE file supplied with this program,
   with the exception of when the original description goes past column 21.
   In this case, the modified country description doesn't fit, and therefore
   the country description in CTYHDG.PRE is used.

2. To allow modification of a file that has previously been updated by CTYHDG,
   the program checks the country description for a '(' character followed by
   any 3 characters, and then ends with the two characters '):'.  This
   combination of charcters is unlikely to be used in any other way within
   the country description, but be aware that a description such as
   GERMANY (GDR): would not work, as the program would change this to
   GERMANY (033): rather than GERMANY (GDR) (033):

3. The CTYHDG.PRE file now contains file update instructions.

On Nov. 28, 1990 I released CTYHDG version 2.01. This version fixes a problem
that shows up with (01e) instead of (100) if the actual calculation was
between 99.96 and 99.99.
******
On Dec. 28, 1990 I released CTYHDG version 3.00 with the following changes:

1. Added support for K8CC's NA program.

2. This version fixes a problem with the prefixes VK, BY, W, UA0 and VE.
   These countries cover more than one zone, and CT will calculate the actual
   zone based on the full prefix entered. An example is, VE6 is zone 4, VE7 is
   zone 3. In CT version 6.22 or older, any beam information added to these
   prefixes prevents this feature from working. This version has the /O option
   which will ignore these prefixes so the zone calculation will work for
   older versions of CT.

3. The program is now simpler to run. The old .CTY file is now copied into a
   .OLD file, and the original .CTY file is changed. No more manual copying.
